# ğŸ›°ï¸ FTP (File Transfer Protocol) - Basics, Setup, and Usage(Centos 09)

---

## ğŸ“Œ What is FTP?

FTP (File Transfer Protocol) is a standard network protocol used to transfer files between a client and a server over a TCP/IP network.

---

## ğŸ§° Common FTP Commands

| Command       | Description                       |
|---------------|-----------------------------------|
| `ftp`         | Start FTP client                  |
| `open`        | Connect to FTP server             |
| `ls` / `dir`  | List files on server              |
| `get`         | Download file from server         |
| `put`         | Upload file to server             |
| `bye` / `quit`| Exit FTP                          |

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ FTP Server Setup on CentOS 9

### âœ… Step 1: Install vsftpd
sudo dnf install vsftpd -y

âœ… Step 2: Start and Enable the FTP Service
#sudo systemctl start vsftpd
#sudo systemctl enable vsftpd

âœ… Step 3: Allow FTP Through Firewall
#sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=ftp
#sudo firewall-cmd --reload

âœ… Step 4: Configure FTP (Optional)
Edit the configuration:
#sudo nano /etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf
Key options:
  anonymous_enable=NO (disable anonymous login)
  local_enable=YES (enable local users)
   write_enable=YES (allow uploads)

Then restart the service:
#sudo systemctl restart vsftpd

ğŸ‘¤ Create FTP User 
#sudo useradd ftpuser
#sudo passwd ftpuser
#sudo mkdir -p /home/ftpuser/ftp_files
#sudo chown ftpuser:ftpuser /home/ftpuser/ftp_files

ğŸ’» FTP Client Usage
ğŸ§ª From Linux terminal:
#ftp <server_ip>
Then log in with the FTP user credentials.

Example session:
Connected to 192.168.1.10
Name: ftpuser
Password:
ftp> ls
ftp> put myfile.txt
ftp> get serverfile.txt
ftp> bye
ğŸ” Secure Alternative: SFTP
Use SFTP over SSH:
#sftp ftpuser@<server_ip>
#SFTP uses port 22 and is encrypted.

ğŸ§¹ Troubleshooting
530 Login incorrect â†’ Check user credentials and permissions.

Connection refused â†’ Ensure vsftpd is running and firewall allows FTP.

Passive mode issues â†’ Enable passive mode ports in vsftpd.conf and firewall.

